\begin{lemma}
[Covering-datum bridge to the open-cover {\v C}ech form]
  \label{lem:cover_datum_bridge}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.coverDatum_bridge}
  \uses{def:basis_cov_system}
  \textit{Project-bespoke compatibility lemma.}
  The injective {\v C}ech-acyclicity Lemma~\ref{lem:injective_cech_acyclic} is stated over an
  open-cover object with a finiteness hypothesis on the index set, whereas the affine cover system's
  admissible coverings are raw covering data \((\iota, U)\) (\(\mathrm{CovDatum}\), with \(\iota\)
  finite, of Definition~\ref{def:basis_cov_system}). This lemma exhibits, for each finite standard
  covering datum, the canonical identification of its section {\v C}ech complex with the section
  {\v C}ech complex of the corresponding open-cover object, so that the {\v C}ech cohomology computed
  in the two presentations agrees.
\end{lemma}
\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:basis_cov_system}
  A standard covering datum \((\iota, U)\) with \(\iota\) finite is precisely the data of a finite
  family of opens \(U : \iota \to \mathrm{Opens}(X)\) whose union is the covered open; this is the
  same underlying data as the open-cover object carried by
  Lemma~\ref{lem:injective_cech_acyclic}. The degreewise products
  \(\prod_\sigma \mathcal{F}(V_\sigma)\) defining the two section {\v C}ech complexes range over the
  same index tuples and use the same face opens \(V_\sigma\), and the coface maps coincide; hence the
  two complexes are identified and their cohomologies agree.
\end{proof}

